      "id": "U3L-READ-1",
      "paper": "review",
      "title": "Mina's Last Game",
      "text": "Mina is the point guard of our school team. Her coach is tough but kind. Before the city game, he warned the players about the hot weather. The heat was terrible that day, and some of them felt tired. Mina had to bear the pain in her knee, but she did not stop. Her goal was simple. She wanted to win for her school. In the second half, our team lacked energy. Then a big crowd of students began to shout. They gave the team a big hand after every point. Mina hit her target and made the last shot. Everyone got up from their seats. It was a pleasant evening for all of us. To many students, Mina is now a symbol of courage."
    }
  ],
